# Orange Thai Curry  

## Ingredients  
- 150 g tofu, cubed  
- 1 onion, chopped  
- 2 carrots, cut into strips  
- 1 tbsp ginger, grated  
- 2 parsnips, cut into strips  
- 100 g green beans, chopped  
- 1 leek, sliced  
- 2 tbsp yellow curry paste  
- 1 can tomatoes (400 g)  
- 1 can coconut milk (400 ml)  
- 1 tbsp oil  

## Preparation  
1. Chop the onion, grate the ginger, and prepare the vegetables.  
2. Fry the tofu in a pan with some oil until golden brown, remove from pan.  
3. Add 1 tbsp of coconut milk, mix well, and set aside.  
4. Sauté the onion and ginger until fragrant.  
5. Add the curry paste and fry briefly.  
6. Add the chopped tomatoes and let them simmer briefly.  
7. Add the vegetables and cook for about 10–15 minutes until tender.  
8. Just before serving, add the remaining coconut milk and fried tofu, mix well.  
9. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot with rice.  

> **Tip:** Add the coconut milk only at the end to preserve its full flavor.  
> **Tip:** Best enjoyed with jasmine or basmati rice.  

## Acknowledgment  
